- !<Text/d25bc418-f2b6-440c-423e-195d56402b14>
  PrefabRemaps:
    []
  Name: Text
  Enabled: true
  RenderOrder: 999
  StretchMode: Stretch
  VerticalAlignment: Center
  HorizontalAlignment: Left
  MeshShadowMode: None
  ShadowColor: {x: 1.000000, y: 1.000000, z: 1.000000, w: 1.000000}
  ShadowDensity: 1.000000
  Text: |-
    Guided Instructions 
     Remove your camera or recreate the same setup you see in this prefab, if you keep both will cause erorrs. There might be duplicate for camera and rendering assets. 
                
                                                                
    Drop any photo of your Nespresso machine (PNG/JPG imported into Assets) into 
      the testTexture slot on SceneController. Press the mic button, ask something
      like "I'm at step 4, what do I do?" — Gemini will respond using the image and
       the full descaling knowledge, and the panel will auto-jump to the detected
      step if you're in AUTO mode.                                                
    
      On device:
    
      Remove testTexture. Press the mic button, ask a question while looking at    
      your machine. Gemini analyzes the live camera frame, places AR labels on
      relevant parts, and the panel tracks your step automatically.                
                                                                
      Manual navigation: tap prev/next buttons to move through all 15 steps. Tap   
      the mode toggle to switch between MANUAL and AUTO.
  Editable: false
  ShowEditingPreview: true
  TouchHandler: !<reference> 00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000000
  SizeToFit: false
  FontSize: 60
